The **NPS (National Pension System) calculator** estimates your retirement corpus based on monthly contributions, current age, retirement age, and expected return rate. At retirement (age 60), 60% of the NPS corpus can be withdrawn as a tax-free lump sum; the remaining 40% is used to purchase an annuity that generates a regular monthly pension.

NPS offers an exclusive additional tax deduction of ₹50,000 under Section 80CCD(1B) — over and above the ₹1.5 lakh Section 80C limit — making it one of the most tax-efficient retirement savings tools in India.
